    "description": "This fixes an issue with installing yt that came up on the users list. When the environment variable CC is set to something with a space in it, the subprocess.call() command will fail with an OSError. This does two things:\r\n\r\n1) It splits the contents of CC before passing it to subprocess, allowing the check to work when people have, for instance, CC set to \"ccache clang\". \r\n2) It disables OpenMP support whenever some other OSError is caught.\r\n\r\n",
